comments.body:
Hannah,

Regarding PPPL's prime contract number, there's no space: DE-AC02-09CH11466

I had discussed with Kate that it seems that some PPPL Collections have it
encoded and some didn't in DataSpace. I think we would want this encoded by
default for all PPPL submissions in any PPPL collection in PDC-Describe.

One suggestion: It seems that the UI would have only a single entry for a
grant. I would recommend changing this to allow for multiple grants. Some
PPPL research have funding through multiple sources. I suspect PU
researchers do as well. So instead of a vertical layout, I recommend
horizontal with the ability to add additional rows, much like how you do
with creator/author metadata. This will provide the greatest granularity.

Cheers,
- Chun

Research Data Developer
Princeton Plasma Physics Laboratory
Performance Assurance & Contract Management

figgy.title: Distinguish between different kinds of resources

comments.body: @hackartisan any way I can help with this?

categories of resources:
- viewable resources (i.e. I go to the resource page and there's a viewer)
  - scanned resource (including recording, archival media, simple)
  - scanned map / raster / vector resources
  - coin, issue, monograph
  - ephemera folder
- container resources - parents to other resources
  - scanned resource mvw
  - scanned map / raster / vector resources
  - numismatic issue
  - ephemera box
- collection resources
  - collection
  - ephemera project
- property resources
  - workflow note
  - ephemera term
  - there are probably lots more of these; nothing really binds them together.


Questions:
- could grouping resources like this help us when updating change sets and decorators?
- why doesn't ephemera folder use common schema?
- why does collection use common schema?

It seems like schemas, change sets, and decorators ought to be more aligned, and more parallel in their organization.

Note that change set has a concept of a core resource: https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/5e0a9321a637de4e7ffbb4b1bd8a59d9efe01d66/app/change_sets/change_set.rb#L39
